### Phase 5 — Category admin, classification, attachments.
###
### Promote admin/agent roles via SQL after registering them.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@customerEmail = customer@example.com
@agentEmail    = agent@example.com
@adminEmail    = admin@example.com
@password      = password123

@customerToken = paste-customer-token
@agentToken    = paste-agent-token
@adminToken    = paste-admin-token
@ticketId      = paste-ticket-uuid
@categoryId    = paste-active-category-uuid
@attachmentId  = paste-attachment-uuid

### 1. Public list of active categories
GET {{host}}/api/v1/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 2. Admin lists all categories (including inactive)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3. Admin creates a category
POST {{host}}/api/v1/admin/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Network",
  "slug": "network",
  "description": "Internet, Wi-Fi, and network access issues"
}

### 4. Admin updates a category (paste id into URL)
PUT {{host}}/api/v1/admin/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Wi-Fi, VPN, DNS and connectivity issues",
  "is_active": true
}

### 5. Admin deactivates a category
DELETE {{host}}/api/v1/admin/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6. Assigned agent updates a ticket's classification
PUT {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/classification
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category_id": "{{categoryId}}",
  "priority": "urgent"
}

### 7. Customer attempts classification (EXPECTED 403)
PUT {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/classification
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "low"
}

### 8. Upload an attachment (PDF / PNG / JPEG / TXT)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/attachments
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----formboundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="screenshot.png"

----formboundary
< ./screenshot.png
----formboundary--

### 9. List attachments
GET {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/attachments
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 10. Download attachment
GET {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/attachments/{{attachmentId}}/download
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 11. Delete attachment (author or admin)
DELETE {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/attachments/{{attachmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
